More arrests are expected in the kidnapping of Cape Town businessperson Ismail Rajah. An intelligence-driven operation involving the Anti-Kidnapping Task Team and members of the Organised Crime Unit, rescued Rajah last week. Ayesha Ismail reports. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - More arrests are expected in the kidnapping of Cape Town businessperson Ismail Rajah. Rajah was abducted in Parow on 9 March, shackled and held hostage in a house in Khayelitsha for more than three months. An intelligence-driven operation involving the Anti-Kidnapping Task Team and members of the Organised Crime Unit, rescued Rajah last week. READ: Kidnapped businessman Ismail Rajah rescued While a ransom demand was made, it was not paid. Four men arrested in connection with the kidnapping have appeared in the Bellville magistrate’s court. They have been remanded in custody until their next court appearance on 11 July. * eNCA's Ayesha Ismail reports.